!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Glasgow JavaScript User Group

    %link{ rel:  "stylesheet/less",
           type: "text/css",
           href: "/stylesheets/styles.less" }

    %script{  type: "text/javascript",
              src:  "http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/less.js/1.3.0/less-1.3.0.min.js" }

    %script{  type: "text/javascript",
              src:  "http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html5shiv/3.6/html5shiv.min.js" }

    %meta{ name: "viewport",
           content: "width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" }

  %body
    %header{class: 'container'}
      %img{src: '/GJS_small.png'}
      %h1{id: 'logo'}
        Glasgow.js
        %br
        %span{class: 'subheading'}The Glasgow JavaScript User Group

      %aside{class: 'hidden-phone'}
        %ul{class: 'nav-pills'}
          %li
            %a{href: '#location'}
              %i{class: "icon-screenshot icon-white"}
              Where?
          %li
            %a{href: 'http://lanyrd.com/2012/glasgowjs/'}
              %i{class: "icon-pencil icon-white"}
              Sign up

    %section{class: 'container', id: 'next-meetup'}
      .row
        .span8
          %h1{id: 'meeting-date'}
            Next Meeting:
            %span{class: 'highlight'}
              Tuesday 4th of December

          %article{id: 'next-meeting'}
            .speaker
              .avatar-container
                %img{class: 'speaker-avatar', src: "https://si0.twimg.com/profile_images/2709718488/b3577ff82d7ce17149c60b584433b798_normal.jpeg"}
              %h2 Entity Systems
              %h3 Jason Frame
              :markdown
                Entity Systems are a game engine architecture pattern. Jason will give us a general overview of entity systems, highlighting the problems they solve and will give us examples of why JS is a cool language to use when implementing them.

              .connect
                %a{href: 'http://jasonframe.co.uk/'}jasonframe.co.uk
                | 
                %a{href: 'https://twitter.com/jaz303'}@jaz303
                |
                %a{href: 'https://github.com/jaz303'}Jason on Github

            .speaker
              %h2 Kata
              :markdown
                We are also going to be doing a kata on the night. This will be decided on the night, so make sure you all bring your laptops along!

              .connect

        .span4
          #sponsors
            %h3 Our Illustrious Sponsors

            %a{href: 'http://emergeadapt.com'}
              %img{src: '/images/emerge-adapt.png', alt: 'EmergeAdapt'}

            %a{href: 'http://newcontext.com'}
              %img{src: '/images/new_context_trimmed.png', alt: 'New Context'}

    #location
      %section{class: 'container'}
        %h1 Where to find us
        .row
          .span4
            :markdown
              ## Strathclyde University
              Graham Hills Building, Room GH510

              The meetup starts at 6:30 with the first session starting at 7pm.

              Let us know you are coming by marking your attendance at [Lanyrd](http://lanyrd.com/2012/glasgowjs/)
          .span8
            :plain
              <iframe width="100%" height="350" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" src="https://maps.google.co.uk/maps?hl=en&amp;safe=off&amp;q=g1+1xp&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=G1+1XP,+United+Kingdom&amp;gl=uk&amp;t=m&amp;z=14&amp;ll=55.860856,-4.241662&amp;output=embed"></iframe>

    #about
      %section{class:'container'}
        .row
          .span4
            :markdown
              ## Sessions
              We don't think it should be all talks and presentations and we intend to include hack sessions, katas over the meetups.

              Any ideas you have for katas or indeed ideas for the meetup in general, please let us know. The Glasgow JS Meetup is 100% aimed at the desires of it's members.

              Just tweet at [@GLWjs](https://twitter.com/GLWjs), or email [info@glasgowjs.com](mailto:info@glasgowjs.com).
          .span4
            :markdown
              ## Presentations
              There are really only a few rules about presenting at Glasgow JS.

              1. You show up
              2. You dont mind the talk being recorded, and put online
              3. No slides. Just code, Browser, Terminal etc.
          .span4
            :markdown
              ## Speaking
              If you are interested in speaking at a meetup pass on your details with [this form](https://docs.google.com/a/glasgowjs.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dHRGay1hUm53aTkxX0JiLTV6RnVwaVE6MQ).

              You can hit us up on twitter, [@GLWjs](https://twitter.com/GLWjs)

              Email [info@glasgowjs.com](mailto:info@glasgowjs.com).

